-- North Sea Statfjord Crude Exports Stable at Six Cargoes in July
-- B y   L a u r a   H u r s t
-- 2013-06-05T15:12:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-05/north-sea-statfjord-crude-exports-stable-at-six-cargoes-in-july.html
Shipments of North Sea Statfjord
crude for July are planned at six cargoes, unchanged from this
month, a loading program obtained by Bloomberg News showed.  The July plan comprises four consignments of 800,000
barrels each and two lots of 855,000 barrels, according to the
schedule.  Loading programs are monthly schedules of crude shipments
compiled by field operators to allow buyers and sellers to plan
their supply and trading activities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Hurst in London at 
 lhurst3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  